commitResults.messageBody:
To fulfill Level-7 requirements, we have to allow for the TaskService to
be able to read from and load, as well as save to the tasklist.txt file

This commit is a work-in-progress commit, and only adds 2 empty files:
1. src/main/java/resources/tasklist.txt
2. src/main/java/service/dbService.java

as well as adding an incomplete private method to TaskService.json
to load tasks from tasklist.txt

commitResults.messageTitle: feat: Allow for storage of tasks in separate file
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks are not persistent across multiple sessions

To improve the user experience and maintain tasks across multiple
sessions, we have to allow for the tasks to be stored somewhere such
that it can be retrieved in future sessions and is constantly updated as
the user adds / removes tasks

A tasklist.txt has been introduced to maintain these tasks and multiple
helper functions have been added to handle the parsing of the
tasklist.txt as well as the updating of the tasklist.txt whenever the
user makes any changes

commitResults.messageTitle: wip: Add support for Dates and Times
commitResults.messageBody: Works for User Input parsing and saving but need to add support for retrieving the task datetime information from tasklist.txt

commitResults.messageTitle: feat: Add support for dates and times
commitResults.messageBody:
The user can provide any string of characters as the date and time of
events and deadlines.

While this simplifies the parsing of user inputs and reduces the code
complexity, there is no checking done regarding the date time and
neither is there a standard format for the user

We add support for the parsing of the user input for the date and times
of events and deadlines, formatting them in the toString() method of
each task type model.

However, it currently relies on the user following a fixed format so as
to avoid DateTimeParseExceptions when parsing the user input which
should be fixed if we would like the user to have greater flexibility
and to reduce the number of false-positive exceptions occurring

The way the folders were originally structured, there was a lot of
coupling between the different packages, etc.

I refactored the folders to contain the purpose rather than the type of
the files within. I.e., rather than having both FeedbackService and
TaskService in /Service, I created two folders, Feedback and Task, to
contain all files related to them in the two folders.

This should reduce coupling between the different files

fix: Mark and unmark task now save in tasklsit.txt
commitResults.messageBody:
A bug was introduced in the master branch when the feature to support
storing tasks in tasklist.txt to ensure persistence was added. Marking
and unmarking of tasks did not update in tasklist.txt, resulting in
errors in listed tasks in future sessions

An additional utility method in FileUtility is added to support the
updating of existing file contents, which is then called by the mark and
unmark task methods in TaskService
